cs.FL, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LO, cs.CC

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with regular languages and automata.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper involves computing the maximal number of atoms and complexities, which can be seen as algorithmic problems.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper discusses the complexity of languages and their quotients, which can be viewed as information-theoretic measures.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is relevant as the paper deals with the logical structure of regular languages and their atoms.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves analyzing the complexity of regular languages and their atoms.
